A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for BookMyShow (Movie Ticket Booking System).

Requirements:

Users can browse movies currently playing in different cities.
Users can view show timings for a movie in a specific theatre.
Users can select seats and book tickets for a show.
Multiple users should not be able to book the same seat at the same time (concurrency handling).
Support seat selection (single or multiple seats).
On successful booking, generate a ticket with booking details.
Handle basic payment flow (assume payment succeeds for LLD).

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is acceptable.
Focus on core booking flow.
Support concurrency (multiple users trying to book same show).

Edge Cases:

Seat already booked by another bookMyShowUser.
Show is full.
Invalid seat selection.
Booking timeout / seat hold expiration.

