C. 6 MANDATORY STEPS FOR LLD DESIGN

1. Clarify requirements

=> Functional: Browse movies, view shows, select seats, book tickets, handle concurrency.
=> Non-Functional: Fast seat availability check, prevent double booking (race condition).
=> Assumptions: Single city for simplicity, payment is mocked, seats are held temporarily.
=> Edge Cases: Seat conflict, show full, booking timeout, invalid seat.

2. Identify entities and relationships

=> Main entities : Movie, Theater, Screen, Show, Seat, Booking, User
=> Key relationships :
Theatre has multiple Screens
Screen has multiple Seats
Show belongs to one Movie + one Screen
Booking contains multiple Seats + one Show + one User

