E. POSSIBLE FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS FROM INTERVIEWER (WITH ANSWERS)

Q1. How did you handle concurrency / double booking?
Answer: Used synchronized on bookTickets() method so only one thread can book for a show at a time.

Q2. What if 1000 users try to book at the same time?
Answer: Synchronized method becomes a bottleneck.
In production, we use Redis + Lua script or database row-level locking for better scalability.

Q3. How would you implement seat hold (temporary reservation)?
Answer: We can add a SeatHold map with timestamp. After 10 minutes, release the hold using a ScheduledExecutorService.

Q4. How would you scale this for high traffic?
Answer: Use Redis for seat inventory with Lua scripts for atomic booking. Main data in sharded database.
Implement Saga pattern for distributed transactions.

Q5. Why is Booking class separate?
Answer: It maintains booking history, status, and user details. It follows Single Responsibility Principle.

Q6. How can you differentiate Customer APIs and Admin APIs ?
=> I have separated user-facing methods and admin methods clearly.
=> In a real system, we would use Role-based access control (RBAC) or separate AdminService and UserService.
For LLD, I have kept them in one service but logically separated them.
Using Interfaces (More Advanced)
interface UserService {
    Booking bookTickets(...);
}

interface AdminService {
    Show addShow(...);
}

class BookMyShowService implements UserService, AdminService { ... }

Q7. Why addShow() should NOT be in Screen class ?

Show is not owned by Screen alone
A Show is a combination of:
Movie
Screen
Show Time (7:30 PM, 10:30 PM, etc.)

One Screen can have multiple shows on the same day (different timings).
One Show belongs to one Movie + one Screen + one Time.
So Show is a separate entity, not just "something inside Screen".
Better Responsibility
Screen should be responsible for seats and layout.
Show should be responsible for which movie is playing at what time on that screen.
BookMyShowService (or a ShowService) should manage the scheduling of shows.

Real-world modeling
In actual BookMyShow / PVR systems, the admin first adds a movie, then creates "Shows" by assigning movie + screen + time.
Shows are not directly added inside Screen object.